I agree entirely.  With PGP legal, PEM is RIPEM's only advantage.
And RIPEM doesn't even do PEM (except the Mac version).
With MIME/PEM arguably slated to overtake PEM, Jeff T. is working 
on adding MIME/PEM to RIPEM.  If he or someone else doesn't
do that or at least add PEM support, then RIPEM doesn't have
much to offer anymore and should quietly go away.
Actually, if we don't make any more progress from where we
are now, I would prefer that RIPEM die, rather than linger
on to muddy the waters.

But, I believe that Jeff is hard at work on RIPEM 2.0, and
there should be good stuff in it.  PEM interoperability 
would be very nice, but I think he's concentrating on 
MIME/PEM.

Mark
